Class BetweenCriteria

All Implemented Interfaces:
Outputable
public class BetweenCriteria
extends Criteria

Class BetweenCriteria is a Criteria extension that generates the SQL syntax for a BETWEEN operator in an SQL Where clause.

Author:
Derek Mahar, Nat Pryce

Constructor Detail

BetweenCriteria

public BetweenCriteria(Matchable operand,
                       Matchable lower,
                       Matchable upper)
Initializes a new BetweenCriteria with an operand and the upper and lower bounds of the SQL BETWEEN operator.

Parameters:
operand - the first operand to the SQL BETWEEN operator that the operator uses to test whether the column falls within the given range. The SQL type of the column must be DECIMAL or NUMERIC.
lower - the lower bound of the BETWEEN operator
upper - the upper bound of the BETWEEN operator
